What happens with AOT?
✔ Angular converts your HTML + TypeScript into JavaScript during build time
AOT = Angular builds your app early so users get a fast experience.
(Not in the browser)

✔ Browser gets fully-prepared code

No extra compilation needed.

✔ App loads faster

Because the user’s browser does less work.

✔ Fewer errors in production

Because Angular catches template mistakes early.



or
“AOT means Angular compiles the application at build time instead of compiling in the browser.
Because the templates and components are already converted into optimized JavaScript before the user loads the app, it makes the application faster, more secure, and reduces bundle size.
Errors are also caught early during build, which makes the production build more reliable.”


-------------------------------------------------------------------


Without AOT (JIT):

User opens your app

Browser starts compiling templates

Takes time

Page loads slowly

With AOT:

Angular compiles everything beforehand

Browser only shows the UI

Page loads very fast